    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is a single-page portfolio with a vertical, scroll-based layout. It is divided into four main sections: Hero (introductory), About, Projects, and Contact. A fixed navigation bar at the top allows users to smoothly scroll to any section. This structure provides a linear, narrative-driven user experience, making it easy to consume information in a logical order while also allowing quick access to specific content. This design was chosen for its simplicity and effectiveness in showcasing a portfolio, as it keeps all content on a single page, eliminating loading times and enhancing user engagement. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: The content is presented through a combination of structured text and responsive grid layouts. Quantitative data is not applicable here, so the focus is on qualitative presentation. The Hero section uses large, impactful text to grab attention. The About section uses a two-column grid to pair text with a placeholder image. The Projects section uses a responsive grid of cards to display project information (title, description, and link). Icons are used to add visual interest to the navigation and contact form. All visual elements are created with HTML/CSS and Unicode, with no external images or SVG files, ensuring fast loading and adaptability. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
